 
<p>
A bill to restore the FCC's power to regulate internet connection
services would enable it to once again require 
<a href="https://www.commondreams.org/newswire/2022/07/18/net-neutrality-and-broadband-justice-act-would-help-protect-internet-users">its weak standard of
"network neutrality".</a>
<p>
This would be a step forward, but nowhere near 
<a href="https://www.techdirt.com/2019/06/18/none-claimed-benefits-killing-net-neutrality-ever-arrived/">far enough to prevent
snooping.<a/>

 